#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""Discover local/remote models and update Pi's ~/.pi/agent/models.json.

This replaces the older get_lm_studio_models.py / get_ollama_models.py split.

Design goals:
- One executable file in ~/.local/bin usable from any working directory.
- Update ~/.pi/agent/models.json directly by default.
- Keep backend-specific behavior explicit via provider kind:
  - lmstudio: OpenAI-compatible /v1/models, LM Studio quirks
  - llamacpp: OpenAI-compatible /v1/models, direct llama.cpp llama-server quirks
  - omlx: llama.cpp-like OpenAI server with template-driven thinking (chat_template_kwargs)
  - ollama: native Ollama metadata API plus Pi OpenAI-compatible provider config
  - vllm: vLLM OpenAI-compatible server using OpenAI-style reasoning/thinking fields
  - vllm-mtp: vLLM with speculative decoding/MTP metrics; OpenAI-style thinking fields
  - openai-compatible: generic OpenAI-compatible /v1/models
  - llamacpp-qwen-mtp: dedicated 8085-sparky Qwen MTP llama.cpp config
- Infer model metadata and thinking controls from provider kind + model name.

Longer documentation:
  ~/.local/bin/pi-coding-agent-config/pi-model-discovery README.md

Usage:
  pi-model-discovery
  pi-model-discovery --dry-run
  pi-model-discovery --provider llama-local=llamacpp:http://127.0.0.1:4321/v1 --dry-run
  pi-model-discovery --only llama-local
  pi-model-discovery --ollama-model qwen3:30b
"""

